comments:
On 30.9.1895 the part in Shropshire  became 
    part of Staffordshire, so that thereafter Bobbington was entirely in Staffordshire. 
    See also Table 2, notes (a) and (c).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Wombourn. See 
    also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, notes (b) and (e) to (k).

Abolished 1.4.1900 and added to the parish of Trysull & Seisdon. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).
